data.title: Martha Coakley Concedes; Charlie Baker Is Your New Governor
data.meta_description: Martha Coakley Concedes; Charlie Baker Is Your New Governor - Westford, MA - The race was one of the closest in recent memory.
data.text:
Attorney General and Democratic gubernatorial candidate Martha Coakley has conceded the race for Massachusetts governor this morning.

Coakley has called Republican Charlie Baker to concede after a long back and forth battle all night that saw Baker and Coakley switch leads as votes trickled in. She will reportedly address supporters and reporters at her Somerville headquarters at 11 a.m. Wednesday morning.

Multiple news organizations called the election to Baker at around midnight, but Coakley said she wanted to wait until the morning for all the votes to be tallied before conceding.

The governorâ€™s race was one the closest statewide results in recent memory.
